      <lg xml:id="TaC3">
<l>kuṟippiṟ koṇṭu neṟippaṭa vulaka</l>
<l>mūṉṟuṭaṉ vaṇaṅku tōṉṟupuka ḻāṇai</l>
<l>meypeṟa naṭāya teyva mūvariṉ</l>
<l>mutalva ṉāki cuṭarviḷaṅ kakalattu</l>
<l>varaipurai tiraipora peruvarai veruvara</l>
<l>vurumura lolimali naḷirkaṭaṟ paṭavara</l>
<l>varacuṭa ṟaṭavarai cuḻaṟṟiya taṉimāt</l>
<l>teyvat taṭiyavark kiṉinā māḷākavē</l>
<l>yicaiyuṅkol lōḻitō ṟūḻiyō vātē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Will it be possible, aeon after aeon, without end,</l>
<l>that we be servants of the servants of the god,</l>
<l>unique [and] great, who made spin the broad mountain with the body of the king</l>
<l>of snakes so that the cool ocean rose, abounding in thunder-sounding sound,</l>
<l>so that the great mountains came to be frightened, while waves dashed against [his]</l>
<l>mountain-like, glowing, shining chest, being the first</l>
<l>of the divine Three who truthfuly carry</l>
<l>[his] overtly famous command to which bow, all three together,</l>
<l>the worlds, so that [they] be kept in order by [his] intentions?</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
